#. type: Title =
#: Tool-White_Balance.markdown.txt:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adjusting white balance\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-White_Balance.markdown.txt:8
msgid ""
"![image](images/Tool-White_Balance-en.png) The **White Balance** tool allows "
"you to adjust the white balance and tint of your photo to compensate for a "
"color cast in the light source such as the blue cast of the sky or tungsten "
"lighting."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-White_Balance.markdown.txt:12
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Note:** For raw photos, you should use the Temperature and Tint\n"
"sliders of the [Raw Adjustments](Tool-Raw_Adjustments.html) tool\n"
"instead.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Tool-White_Balance.markdown.txt:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "To adjust the white balance of your photo:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-White_Balance.markdown.txt:17
msgid "![image](images/Button-White_Balance.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-White_Balance.markdown.txt:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1.  Click the white balance tool button in the [tool\n"
"    bar](Tools-Editing.html). (A new white balance tool will appear at\n"
"    the top of the [tool stack](Tool_Stack.html).)\n"
"2.  Do either of the following:\n"
"    1.  Use the Temperature and Tint sliders to adjust the white balance\n"
"        and tint.\n"
"    2.  Click the eyedropper button inside the tool (the mouse will\n"
"        change to an eyedropper), then click somewhere on your photo\n"
"        that you want to be neutral gray. (Your photo's colors will then\n"
"        shift accordingly.) When satisfied with the color cast\n"
"        reduction, click the eyedropper button again to complete the\n"
"        adjustment.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-White_Balance.markdown.txt:37
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"3.  Optionally:\n"
"    -   Create a mask using [regions](Regions.html).\n"
"    -   Select a different [blend mode](Blend_Modes.html).\n"
"    -   Adjust the [Opacity slider](Tool_Anatomy.html#Opacity).\n"
"    -   Make a [color/luminosity](Color_Luminosity_Selection.html)\n"
"        selection.\n"
msgstr ""

